Werbung/Ad ✨ IMPRESSIONS, part 7

Three MICHELIN starred restaurant BOURY by TIM BOURY in Roeselare, Belgium.

The „power trio“ TIM BOURY, his wife INGE WAELES and his brother BEN BOURY have created a place of bliss for foodies from all over the world with their entire team in the Belgian-Flemish province! The modern French cuisine inspires on absolute world-class level and interprets dishes in a new way.

In the dishes of TIM, classics are mixed with new and creative momentum and, if possible, ingredients from the region are used. For example, the very rare hop sprouts were an ingredient in the excellent langoustine dish. These have only one season of two weeks a year. Best ingredients are perfectly balanced with great aromatics, different textures and temperatures and then beautifully presented! A perfect taste experience!

World-class food requires a wine pairing on the same level. Sommelier PIETER GODTS is distinguished by a lot of expertise and even more dedication. 

The service team under the leadership of INGE acts extremely attentively and with a lot of pleasure in the profession! This is transferred to the guests and makes a visit a great overall experience.

To round off a lunch or dinner perfectly, you can spend the night in one of the three very tastefully furnished rooms or in the loft. The delicious breakfast is served in the room enthusiastically in the same way as the food in the restaurant!

Many thanks to INGE, TIM, BEN and to the entire team of BOURY for a fantastic dinner, warm service and very generous hospitality!

BEN is also responsible for BOURY ACADEMY! In this, chefs from all over the world are further qualified in 3 months including certificate and are then sought-after chefs worldwide!

